details.name: Felipe Drugovich
details.text: Felipe Drugovich Roncato (born 23 May 2000, in Maringá, Paraná, Brazil) is a Brazilian racing driver  who is competing in Formula 2 with MP Motorsport.

details.name: Martin Brundle
details.text: Martin John Brundle (born 1 June 1959) is a British former racing driver, best known as a Formula One driver and as a commentator for ITV Sport from 1997 to 2008, the BBC from 2009 to 2011, and Sky Sports since 2012.Brundle contested the 1983 British Formula Three Championship, finishing a close second to Ayrton Senna, and the two progressed to Formula One the next year.

details.name: Théo Pourchaire
details.text: Théo Jérôme Julien Pourchaire (born 20 August 2003) is a French racing driver, currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship for the ART Grand Prix team.

details.name: Charles Leclerc
details.text: Charles Marc Hervé Perceval Leclerc (French pronunciation: ​[ʃaʁl ləklɛʁ]; born 16 October 1997) is a Monégasque racing driver, currently racing in Formula One for Scuderia Ferrari, contracted until the end of the 2024 season.

details.name: Death of Ayrton Senna
details.text: On 1 May 1994, Brazilian Formula One driver Ayrton Senna was killed after his car crashed into a concrete barrier while he was leading the 1994 San Marino Grand Prix at the Autodromo Enzo e Dino Ferrari in Italy.

details.name: Oscar Piastri
details.text: Oscar Piastri (born 6 April 2001) is an Australian racing driver who serves as the Reserve Driver for the Alpine F1 Team, having previously been in the team's driver academy.

details.name: Nigel Mansell
details.text: Nigel Ernest James Mansell,  (; born 8 August 1953) is a British former racing driver who won both the Formula One World Championship (1992) and the CART Indy Car World Series (1993).

details.name: Mario Andretti
details.text: Mario Gabriele Andretti (born February 28, 1940) is an Italian-born American former racing driver.

details.name: Rubens Barrichello
details.text: Rubens "Rubinho" Gonçalves Barrichello (Portuguese pronunciation: [ˈʁubẽjz ɡõ'sawviz baʁiˈkɛlʊ], [ʁuˈbĩjʊ]; born 23 May 1972) is a Brazilian racing driver who competed in Formula One between 1993 and 2011.

details.name: Michael Schumacher
details.text: Michael Schumacher (; German: [ˈmɪçaːʔeːl ˈʃuːmaxɐ] (listen); born 3 January 1969) is a German former racing driver who competed in Formula One for Jordan, Benetton, Ferrari, and Mercedes.

details.name: Dan Ticktum
details.text: Daniel Charles Anthony Ticktum (born 8 June 1999) is a British racing driver currently racing with the NIO 333 FE Team in the Formula E World Championship.Ticktum became a member of the Red Bull Junior Team in 2017.

details.name: Robert Shwartzman
details.text: Robert Mikhailovich Shwartzman (Russian: Ро́берт Миха́йлович Шва́рцман, IPA: [ˈrobʲɪrt mʲɪˈxajləvʲɪtɕ ˈʂvartsmɐn]; born 16 September 1999) is a Russo-Israeli racing driver who competed in the FIA Formula 2 Championship for 2020 and 2021 where he finished 4th and 2nd respectively.

details.name: Antonio Giovinazzi
details.text: Antonio Maria Giovinazzi (Italian pronunciation: [anˈtɔːnjo dʒoviˈnattsi]; born 14 December 1993) is an Italian racing driver who is currently racing for Dragon/Penske Autosport in Formula E. He was the 2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship runner-up and raced with Prema in the 2016 GP2 Series, again finishing runner-up with five wins and eight overall podiums.

details.name: Yuki Tsunoda
details.text: Yuki Tsunoda (Japanese: 角田 裕毅, Tsunoda Yūki; born 11 May 2000) is a Japanese racing driver who is racing for Scuderia AlphaTauri in Formula One.

details.name: Olivier Beretta
details.text: Olivier Beretta (born 23 November 1969) is a professional racing driver from Monaco who raced in Formula One in 1994 for the Larrousse team, partnering Érik Comas.

details.name: Robert Kubica
details.text: Robert Józef Kubica (Polish pronunciation: [ˈrɔbɛrt kuˈbit͡sa] (listen); born 7 December 1984) is a Polish racing driver.

details.name: Zhou Guanyu
details.text: Zhou Guanyu (Chinese: 周冠宇; pinyin: Zhōu Guànyǔ; born 30 May 1999) is a Chinese racing driver who currently competes in Formula One for Alfa Romeo.

details.name: Kimi Räikkönen
details.text: Kimi-Matias Räikkönen (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈkimi ˈmɑtiɑs ˈræi̯kːønen]; born 17 October 1979), nicknamed "The Iceman", is a Finnish racing driver who competed in Formula One between 2001 and 2021 for Sauber, McLaren, Ferrari, Lotus, and Alfa Romeo.

details.name: Kamui Kobayashi
details.text: Kamui Kobayashi (小林 可夢偉, Kobayashi Kamui, born 13 September 1986) is a Japanese professional racing driver who competes in the FIA World Endurance Championship for Toyota Gazoo Racing (GR) and in the Super Formula Championship for KCMG as of 2021.

details.name: Luca Ghiotto
details.text: Luca Ghiotto (born 24 February 1995) is an Italian racing driver who last competed in Formula 2 for Hitech Grand Prix.

details.name: Jacky Ickx
details.text: Jacques Bernard "Jacky" Ickx (French pronunciation: ​[ʒaki ɪks]; born 1 January 1945) is a Belgian former racing driver who won the 24 Hours of Le Mans six times (second-highest of all time) and achieved eight wins and 25 podium finishes in Formula One.

details.name: Juan Pablo Montoya
details.text: Juan Pablo Montoya Roldán (Spanish pronunciation: [ˈxwan ˈpaβlo monˈtoʝa rolˈdan]; born September 20, 1975) is a Colombian racing driver.

details.name: Nico Hülkenberg
details.text: Nicolas Hülkenberg (German pronunciation: [ˈniːko ˈhʏlkənbɛɐ̯k], born 19 August 1987) is a German professional racing driver who currently serves as the reserve driver in Formula One for the Aston Martin F1 Team.

details.name: René Arnoux
details.text: René Alexandre Arnoux (born 4 July 1948) is a French former racing driver who competed in 12 Formula One seasons (1978 to 1989).

details.name: Mick Schumacher
details.text: Mick Schumacher (German pronunciation: [ˈmɪk ˈʃuːmaxɐ]; born 22 March 1999) is a German racing driver.

details.name: Damon Hill
details.text: Damon Graham Devereux Hill,  (born 17 September 1960) is a British former racing driver from England and the 1996 Formula One World Champion.

details.name: David Coulthard
details.text: David Marshall Coulthard  (; born 27 March 1971) is a British former racing driver from Scotland, later turned presenter, commentator and journalist.

details.name: JJ Lehto
details.text: Jyrki Juhani Järvilehto (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈjyrki ˈjærʋilehto]; born 31 January 1966), better known as "JJ Lehto", is a Finnish racing driver.

details.name: Thierry Boutsen
details.text: Thierry Marc Boutsen (born 13 July 1957) is a Belgian former racing driver who raced for the Arrows, Benetton, Williams, Ligier and Jordan teams in Formula One.

details.name: Frederik Vesti
details.text: Frederik Vesti (born 13 January 2002) is a Danish racing driver competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with ART Grand Prix.

details.name: Jüri Vips
details.text: Jüri Vips (born 10 August 2000) is an Estonian racing driver, currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Hitech Grand Prix.

details.name: Christian Lundgaard
details.text: Christian Lundgaard (born 23 July 2001) is a Danish racing driver who is driving the No.

details.name: Olli Caldwell
details.text: Oliver "Olli" Caldwell (born 11 June 2002) is a British racing driver currently racing in the Formula 2 Championship with Campos Racing.

details.name: Clément Novalak
details.text: Clément Novalak (born 23 December 2000) is a French-Swiss racing driver currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship for MP Motorsport.

details.name: Logan Sargeant
details.text: Logan Hunter Sargeant (born December 31, 2000) is an American racing driver.

details.name: Ralph Boschung
details.text: Ralph Boschung (born 23 September 1997) is a Swiss racing driver who is competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship for Campos Racing.

details.name: Marcus Armstrong
details.text: Marcus Armstrong (born 29 July 2000) is a New Zealand motor racing driver who competes in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Hitech Grand Prix.

details.name: Calan Williams
details.text: Calan Williams (born 30 June 2000) is an Australian racing driver who is currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Trident.

details.name: David Beckmann
details.text: David Alexander Beckmann (born 27 April 2000) is a German racing driver.

details.name: Amaury Cordeel
details.text: Amaury Cordeel (born 9 July 2002) is a Belgian racing driver who currently competes in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Van Amersfoort Racing.

details.name: Liam Lawson
details.text: Liam Lawson (born 11 February 2002) is a New Zealand motor racing driver, mentored by three-time New Zealand Grand Prix winner Ken Smith.

details.name: Riccardo Patrese
details.text: Riccardo Gabriele Patrese (born 17 April 1954) is an Italian former racing driver, who raced in Formula One from 1977 to 1993.

details.name: Alain Prost
details.text: Alain Marie Pascal Prost (French: [alɛ̃ pʁɔst]; born 24 February 1955) is a French retired racing driver and Formula One team owner.

details.name: Callum Ilott
details.text: Callum Ilott (born 11 November 1998) is a British racing driver competing in the NTT IndyCar Series for Juncos Hollinger Racing.

details.name: Brendon Hartley
details.text: Brendon Hartley (born 10 November 1989) is a New Zealand professional racing driver who is currently competing in the FIA World Endurance Championship with Toyota Gazoo Racing.

details.name: Lando Norris
details.text: Lando Norris (; born 13 November 1999) is a British-Belgian racing driver currently competing in Formula One with McLaren, racing under the British flag.

details.name: Richard Verschoor
details.text: Richard Verschoor (born 16 December 2000) is a Dutch racing driver, currently competing for Trident Racing in the Formula 2 Championship.

details.name: Johnny Herbert
details.text: John Paul "Johnny" Herbert (born 25 June 1964) is a British former racing driver and current television announcer for Sky Sports F1.

details.name: Jake Hughes
details.text: Jake Hughes (born 30 May 1994) is a British racing driver and winner of the inaugural BRDC Formula 4 Championship.

details.name: Enzo Fittipaldi
details.text: Enzo Fittipaldi da Cruz (born 18 July 2001) is a Brazilian-American racing driver, the grandson of two time Formula 1 champion Emerson Fittipaldi by his daughter Juliana and Carlos da Cruz, and brother of racing driver Pietro Fittipaldi.

details.name: Cem Bölükbaşı
details.text: Cem Bölükbaşı (Turkish pronunciation: [dʒæm bœlykˈbaʃɯ]; born 9 February 1998) is a Turkish racing driver and former sim-racer who currently competes in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Charouz Racing System.

details.name: MP Motorsport
details.text: MP Motorsport is a Dutch auto racing team currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship.

details.name: Virtuosi Racing
details.text: Virtuosi Racing (previously known as Virtuosi UK, and UNI Virtuosi in Formula 2) is a British racing team currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship.

details.name: Jehan Daruvala
details.text: Jehan Daruvala (born 1 October 1998) is an Indian racing driver currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Prema Racing.

details.name: Dennis Hauger
details.text: Dennis Hauger (born 17 March 2003) is a Norwegian racing driver currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Prema Racing.

details.name: Ayumu Iwasa
details.text: Ayumu Iwasa (岩佐 歩夢)(born 22 September 2001) is a Japanese racing driver currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with DAMS.

details.name: Jack Doohan (racing driver)
details.text: Jack Doohan (born 20 January 2003) is an Australian race car driver currently competing in the FIA Formula 2 Championship with Virtuosi Racing.
